
Collections are a group of same or different kind of data.
There are two types of collections in Kotlin:

1. Collections of the same element (or one type of data)
   + IntArray --> Integer
   + BooleanArray --> Boolean
   + DoubleArray --> Double
   + ByteArray --> Byte
   + LongArray --> Long
   + ShortArray --> Short
   + FloatArray --> Float

2. Immutable Collection --> Only read the values but cannot write to it
   + List --> listOf //Similar to arrayOf but with less helper methods and size can be easily increased when needed
   + Set --> setOf
   + Map --> mapOf

3. Mutable Collections
   + Mutable List --> ArrayList, arrayListOf, mutableListOf
   + Mutable Set --> mutableSetOf, hashSetOf
   + Mutable Map --> HashMap, hasMapOf, mutableMapOf